<table role="presentation" style="width:94%;max-width:600px;border:none;border-spacing:0;text-align:left;font-family:Arial,sans-serif;font-size:16px;line-height:22px;color:#363636;">
    <tbody>
        <tr>
            <td style="padding:30px;background-color:#ffffff;">
                <p style='font-size: 18pt;color:#234075;font-weight: bold;'>Submission Successful</p>
                <p style='font-size: 13pt;color:#00a6ed;font-weight: bold;'>Your Emergency Support Services (ESS) File Number is: {{fileNumber}}</p>
                <p><strong>Thank you for completing your needs assessment interview with an ESS Responder. Please keep a record of your Emergency Support Services File Number as you will need this when you connect with an ESS Responder in the future.</strong></p>
                <div style="background-color:cornsilk;">
                    <p style='font-size: 16pt;color:#00a6ed;font-weight: bold;'><img src="data:image/jpeg;charset=utf-8;base64,{{attentionImage}}" alt="!">Next Steps if you are under EVACUATION ORDER:</p>
                    <ul>
                        <li>
                            If you require emergency supports, review your evacuation order and proceed to your nearest Reception Centre. A list of open Reception Centres can be found at <a href="https://www.emergencyinfobc.gov.bc.ca/" style="color:#00a6ed;text-decoration:underline;">Emergency Info BC</a>.
                        </li>
                        <br>
                        <li>
                            To qualify for Emergency Support Services (ESS), you will need to connect with an ESS Responder and complete a needs assessment interview. The needs assessment is what determines your eligibility for supports.
                        </li>
                        <br>
                        <li>
                            Any goods and services obtained prior to a needs assessment interview are not eligible for retroactive reimbursement.
                        </li>
                        <br>
                        <li>
                            If <strong>NO</strong> nearby Reception Centre is open and immediate action is required, please contact your Local Emergency Program for next steps.
                        </li>
                        <br>
                    </ul>
                </div>
                <p style='font-size: 16pt;color:#00a6ed;font-weight: bold;'>Next Steps if you are under EVACUATION ALERT:</p>
                <ul>
                    <li>
                        If you <strong>DO NOT</strong> require emergency serves at this time, no further action is required. If your Alert turns into an ORDER – please see the above actions.
                    </li>
                </ul>
                <br />
                <p>
                    <strong>
                        Already have an account in the Evacuee Registration & Assistance Tool? Please use the following link to login to the tool and review and/or edit your new ESS File:
                        <a href='https://ess.gov.bc.ca' style="color:#00a6ed;text-decoration:underline;">https://ess.gov.bc.ca</a>
                        <br /><i style="color: #808080">(select the 'Already have an account? Log in' button)</i>
                    </strong>
                </p>
                <br/>
                <p>If you need help with your Evacuee Registration and Assistance (ERA) profile or Service BC authentication, please contact our toll-free support line at 1-800-387-4258. Our support team is available: Monday to Friday: 7:30 AM to 5:00 PM (excluding statutory holidays).</p>
            </td>
        </tr>
